    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1805_10_03_page01.jpg"/>
                
                        <opener>
                        <dateline> 
                        <note>1</note>
                       <date when="1805-10-03">Oct 3<hi rend="superscript">d. </hi> 1805</date></dateline>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworthstown</placeName>
                        D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> . <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DumoE1">Sir</persName></opener>
                        <p>
                        I took much pains<lb/>
                        to find you in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName> last<lb/>
                        June &amp; July; I hear that you<lb/>
                        are now in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#IE">Ireland</placeName> &amp; I send<lb/>
                        this letter to take its chance<lb/>
                        of finding you - I begged<lb/>
                        <persName ref="./Personography.xml#GratH1" cert="medium">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>Grattan</persName> to remind <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LansH1">Sir<lb/>
                        Henry Petty</persName> of our family,<lb/>
                        who was <add><unclear>at Parsson</unclear></add> <del>at</del> a glimpse of what<lb/>
                        all the world now see in full<lb/>
                        blaze - I do assure you my<lb/>
                        D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir that we value you most<lb/>
                        highly &amp; that we should be truly<lb/>
                        proud &amp; what is better truly hap-<lb/>
                        py to see you here - a large<lb/>
                    
                    <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1805_10_03_page02.jpg"/>
                        <add>family</add> fond of literature &amp; some of them<lb/>
                        known in its republic, who live<lb/>
                        from choice in retirement is<lb/>
                        a spectacle which neither you<lb/>
                        nor <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LansH1">L<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> Henry</persName> can often see -<lb/></p>
                        <p>
                        We live within a days<lb/>
                        journey of <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin_IE">Dublin</placeName> &amp; I am<lb/>
                        seldom from home<lb/></p>
                        <closer>
                        I am D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir<lb/>
                        Yours sincerely<lb/>
                        <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">Rich<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> Lovell Edgeworth</persName><lb/></closer>
                    
                    <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1805_10_03_page03.jpg"/>
                      
                      <closer>
                        <address>
                        <addrLine><persName ref="./Personography.xml#DumoE1">a Monsieur</persName></addrLine>
                        <addrLine><persName ref="./Personography.xml#DumoE1">Monsieur Dumont</persName></addrLine>
                       <addrLine>&amp;c &amp;c &amp;c</addrLine>
                      </address></closer>
                

                        
                    
                
                    
                  
                
            </div>
        </body>
